      <div type="description" n="monument">
        <head>Description of Monument</head>
        <p>A rectangular <rs type="objectType">statue base</rs> without moulding, recomposed from two fragments (<measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="width">1.05</measure> × <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height">0.61</measure> × <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="depth">0.575</measure>).</p>
      </div>

      <div type="description" n="text">
        <head>Description of Text</head>
        <p>i. is  inscribed on the front face, whose rough surface may indicate that a previous inscription had been erased; the surface has been worn away by water at the left side. ii. is cut on the right side, on a surface from which a previous text appears to have been erased, and which is oddly pitted.</p>
      </div>

      <div type="description" n="letters">
        <head>Description of Letters</head>
        <p n="036">i. Av. <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height" precision="circa">0.035</measure>; irregular, elongated. ii. Roughly cut; <measure dim="height" type="length" unit="metre">0.035-0.065</measure> (<term>phi</term>), cross <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height">0.17</measure>.</p>
      </div>

      <div type="description" n="date">
        <head>Date</head>
        <p n="036">i. <date notAfter="0414" exact="both" precision="circa" notBefore="0405">A.D. 405/414</date> (<rs type="criteria">prosopography</rs>); ii. <date notAfter="0600" exact="none" notBefore="0401">fifth to sixth centuries A.D.</date> or later (<rs type="criteria">lettering</rs>)</p>
      </div>

      <div lang="grc" n="text" type="edition">
        <head lang="en">Edition</head>
        <div type="textpart_section" n="i"><lg met="elegaic">
       <lb n="1"/><l met="hexameter"><orig n="unresolved"><unclear reason="damage">θεμ</unclear><gap agent="damage" extent="1" reason="lost" unit="character"/><unclear reason="damage">ιι</unclear>ι<gap agent="damage" extent="1" reason="lost" unit="character"/><unclear reason="damage">καιιι</unclear>ιν</orig> <w lemma="σύ">σε</w> <w lemma="φάλαγξ">φάλαγξ</w> <w lemma="ἵστημι">ἔστησεν</w>, <rs type="official-secul" key="PPO"><w lemma="ὕπαρχος">ὕπαρχε</w></rs>,</l>
       <lb n="2"/><l met="pentameter"><w lemma="ἀντί">ἀντ'</w> <w lemma="εὐεργεσία">εὐεργεσιῶν</w> <w lemma="μικρός">μικρὰ</w> <w lemma="δίδωμι">δίδουσα</w> <w lemma="γέρας">γέρα</w></l>
       <lb n="3"/><l met="hexameter"><persName type="aphrodisian" key="Anthemius" full="yes"><name reg="Ἀνθέμιος">Ἀν<unclear reason="damage">θ</unclear>έμ<unclear reason="damage">ι</unclear>ε</name></persName>, <w lemma="σῴζω"><supplied reason="lost">σ</supplied><unclear reason="damage">ῴ</unclear>ζων</w> <w lemma="γάρ">γὰρ</w> <w lemma="ὁμοῦ">ὁμοῦ</w> <w lemma="δῆμος">δήμους</w> <w lemma="τε">τε</w> <w lemma="πόλις">πόλεις</w> <w lemma="τε">τε</w></l>
       <lb n="4"/><l met="pentameter"><w lemma="ἐρύω">ῥύσαο</w> <w lemma="καί">κ<unclear reason="damage">α</unclear>ὶ</w> <rs reg="provincial council" key="koinon" type="subject"><w lemma="Κᾶρ"><placeName type="ethnic" full="yes" reg="Κάρ">Καρῶν</placeName></w></rs> <w lemma="τάξις">τάξιν</w> <w lemma="ἀπόλλυμι">ἀπολλυμένην</w>,</l>
       <lb n="5"/><l met="hexameter"><w lemma="ὅς">ἣν</w> <persName type="aphrodisian" key="Beronicianus" full="yes"><name reg="Βερονικιανός">Βερο<unclear reason="damage">νικ</unclear>ι<unclear reason="damage">αν</unclear>ὸς</name></persName> <w lemma="διέπω">διέπων</w> <w lemma="θρόνος">θρόνον</w>
         <lb n="6"/><space dim="horizontal"/> <rs type="official-secul" key="praeses"><w lemma="ἡγεμονεύς">ἡγεμον<unclear reason="damage">ῆ</unclear>ος</w></rs> <space dim="horizontal"/></l>
       <lb n="7"/><l met="pentameter"><w lemma="ἄνωγα">ἤνωγεν</w> <w lemma="τεύχω">τε<unclear reason="damage">ύ</unclear>χειν</w> <w lemma="εἰκών">εἰκόνα</w> <w lemma="μαρμάρεος">μαρμαρέη<supplied reason="lost">ν</supplied></w></l>
        </lg></div>
		<div type="textpart_section" n="ii"><ab>
		<lb n="1"/><w lemma="φῶς">Φῶς</w> <g type="cross"/> <w lemma="ΧΜΓ"><abbr>Χ</abbr><abbr>Μ</abbr><abbr>Γ</abbr></w>·
		<lb n="2"/><w lemma="ζωή">Ζωή</w></ab></div>
      </div>

      

      <div type="translation">
        <head>Translation</head>
        <ab n="036">i. The array <supplied reason="subaudible" cert="low">of the Carians</supplied> set up your statue, prefect, giving a small reward for your benefactions; for, Anthemios, saving peoples and cities, you also rescued the order of the Carians, which was being destroyed, to whom <supplied reason="subaudible">the Carians</supplied> Beronikianos, occupying the seat of governor, gave instructions to make a marble statue.</ab>
        <ab n="144">ii. Light! Life! <persName key="Mary" type="divine" full="yes">M<supplied reason="abbreviation">ary</supplied></persName> b<supplied reason="abbreviation">ore</supplied> <persName key="Christ" type="divine" full="yes">Ch<supplied reason="abbreviation">rist</supplied></persName>.</ab>
      </div>

      <div type="apparatus">
        <head>Apparatus</head>
        <p n="036">i. l. 1,  Perhaps <foreign lang="grc"><unclear reason="damage">Κα</unclear>ρ<unclear reason="damage">ῶ</unclear>ν σε φάλαγξ</foreign>, although this seems clumsily repetitious.</p>
        <p n="144">ii. There are traces around the cross which might be decoration or a monogram.</p><p>ii. l. 1, perhaps <foreign lang="grc"><persName key="Christ" type="divine" full="yes"><expan><abbr>Χ</abbr><supplied reason="abbreviation">ριστὸν</supplied></expan></persName> <persName key="Mary" type="divine" full="yes"><expan><abbr>Μ</abbr><supplied reason="abbreviation">αρία</supplied></expan></persName> <expan><abbr>Γ</abbr><supplied reason="abbreviation">εννᾳ</supplied></expan></foreign></p>
      </div><div type="commentary">
        <head>Commentary</head>
        <p>For i. see discussion at <xref type="eAla-text" n="IV.4">IV.4</xref>. The man honoured is the PPO Anthemios (405-414; PLRE II, Anthemius 1).</p>
        <p>For ii. see discussion at <xref type="eAla-text" n="VIII.16">VIII.16</xref> and <xref type="eAla-text" n="VIII.20">VIII.20</xref>.</p>
      
        </div>

      <div type="history" n="locations"><head>Locations</head><p>Found: <rs type="found"><rs type="monuList">South Agora, Agora Gate</rs>: during excavation of the collecting pool.</rs>. Original location: <rs type="origLocation">Unknown.</rs>. Last recorded location: <rs type="lastLocation">Museum (1993).</rs>. </p></div>

      

      

      <div type="history" n="record">
        <head>History of Recording</head>
        <p>Excavated by the NYU expedition in 1977 (<rs type="invNo">77.76</rs>, SBI <rs type="sbi">47</rs>).</p>
      </div>

